        <p>Nobody in the appliance repair industry talks about what agricultural proximity does to household appliances. In Moorpark, we deal with the consequences on nearly every call.</p>

        <p>The Tierra Rejada Valley is one of the most actively farmed areas in Ventura County. The fine agricultural dust &mdash; a mix of soil particulate, pollen, and organic matter from orchards and fields &mdash; doesn't stop at property lines. It gets pulled into refrigerator condenser compartments through the intake vents, accumulates in dryer lint paths beyond what the lint trap catches, and coats range hood filters. In homes backing up to agricultural land, we find condenser coils that are completely packed within 4&ndash;6 months of the last cleaning. In a typical suburban home, that same level of accumulation might take 12&ndash;18 months.</p>

        <p>A packed condenser coil forces the compressor to run longer and harder to maintain temperature. On a GE or Whirlpool refrigerator, this increases energy consumption noticeably. On a Sub-Zero, where the compressor is a $900+ part, the stakes are higher. Either way, a $150 coil cleaning prevents a $500&ndash;$1,200 compressor failure. We'll always be honest about whether your specific location warrants more frequent maintenance.</p>

        <p>Calleguas hard water is the second factor. The mineral content causes inlet valve calcification on washers and dishwashers, scale buildup on dishwasher heating elements, and restricted flow in ice maker water lines. We see these patterns weekly in 93021.</p>

